home inbal halperin landsberg i am a postdoc in the helix group which is part of russ altman s lab the lab is located at the clark center home to the biox program in stanford university my current research focus is protein function prediction the research is performed as part of the feature project my phd thesis is on improved docking schemes utilizing biological information it proposes 3 methods for predicting protein binding sites each method is based on a different type of data 1 phage display results sitelight 2 coupling of conserved residues across interfaces 3 inter molecular correlated mutations this thesis was done under the supervision of prof ruth nussinov & prof haim wolfson at the bioinfo3d group in tel aviv university thesis docking review publication list ikkha peru machu pichu peru jiuzhaigou china ayutthaya thailand
